description.plain:
Isis Gatson (born January 1, 2000), better known as Ice Spice, is a rapper from the Bronx, New York City.

Ice Spice began rapping in 2021, inspired by New York artists such as Nicki Minaj and Cardi B. Her confident lyrics are accompanied by the production that defines her sound, courtesy of her in-house producer, Riot.

Her August 2022 single, the upbeat drill song “Munch (Feelin' U),” brought her internet virality. The track hit 2.2 million views on YouTube in two weeks and was co-signed by Drake.

songs.title: Munch (Feelin’ U)

description.plain:
“Munch (Feelin' U)” is the breakout single by Bronx rapper Ice Spice. Released in August 2022, the track went viral shortly thereafter due to its quotable chorus:

You thought I was feelin' you?
That nigga a munch
Nigga a eater, he ate it for lunch
Bitch, I’m a baddie, I get what I want



Shortly after the song’s release, it caught the attention of Drake, who played the song on OVO Sound Radio and flew Ice Spice out to Toronto to party with him.

songs.title: Bikini Bottom

description.plain:
Following up her breakout single “Munch (Feelin' U),” “Bikini Bottom” sees Ice Spice rapping about her lifestyle worth of her new-found fame, partying and expensive fashion. The title of the track is named after the Bikini Bottom city, the main setting used in the show SpongeBob SquarePants.

On October 11, 2022, Ice Spice took to Instagram previewing the first thirty seconds of the song. That same day, Ice Spice took to Twitter talking about the song, stating:

that song called bikini bottom 😭spongebob my fav show idc idc

On October 25, 2022, Ice Spice took to Instagram revealing the song’s release date (October 28) and cover art.
